gomodel:SYNGO_4978  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunogold EM of rat spinal cord showed substance P (gene TAC1) and serotonin particles at large dense core vesicles in the same presynape. The presented EM image does not show a postsynaptic structure, authors comment on this and mention this was observed in multiple images (data not shown).\n\nSimilarly, Bolam et al. (PMID:2454839) reported presynaptic substance P was observed at symmetric synapses in rat neostriatum.. Experimental description: \"Adult male rats were fixed by perfusion in 300 ml of glutaraldehyde in 0.1 M cacodylate buffer (pH 7.6); raphe nuclei of the medulla oblongata and ventral horn of the spinal cord were carefully dissected and post-fixed by immersion for 1 h in 0.5% OS04 diluted in the same cacodylate buffer.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4978" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

